National Security Advisor to the Vice President, Dr. Phil Gordon, held a meeting with Partnership for Central America (PCA) leaders Ajay Banga and Ray Chambers, CEOs from companies that have responded to the Vice President's Call to Action for Northern Central America, and senior U.S. government officials. The purpose of the meeting was to discuss mobilizing investments to address the root causes of migration. The Call to Action has already generated over $3.2 billion in private sector investments to promote economic opportunity in northern Central America. The meeting participants agreed to enhance collaboration under this public-private partnership to create more opportunities for the people in the region. They also discussed combating corruption, promoting human rights and labor rights, and upholding the rule of law as part of the broader strategy to address the root causes of migration. Additionally, the importance of promoting opportunities for women and upholding social responsibility was emphasized.